<span id="freeTextContainer5918079408507383114">Rasana Atreya&apos;s debut novel, Tell A Thousand Lies, was shortlisted for the UK-based &quot;Tibor Jones South Asia Prize.&quot; In 2017, the University of New Mexico, Albuquerque, taught this novel to the students of &quot;English 479.&quot; <br/><br/>Glam Magazine, UK (June 2014) calls &quot;Tell A Thousand Lies&quot; one of their &quot;five favourite tales from India.&quot;<br/><br/>She&apos;s currently working on the series, &quot;Tales From The Deccan Plateau&quot;:<br/>* T</span>
  <span id="freeText5918079408507383114" style="display:none">Rasana Atreya's debut novel, Tell A Thousand Lies, was shortlisted for the UK-based "Tibor Jones South Asia Prize." In 2017, the University of New Mexico, Albuquerque, taught this novel to the students of "English 479." <br /><br />Glam Magazine, UK (June 2014) calls "Tell A Thousand Lies" one of their "five favourite tales from India."<br /><br />She's currently working on the series, "Tales From The Deccan Plateau":<br />* Tell A Thousand Lies<br />* Talking Is Wasted Breath<br />* Daughters Inherit Silence<br />* The Temple Is Not My Father<br />* The Water Wives<br />* Tell A Lie, Beget A Daughter<br /><br />Rasana is one of India's self-publishing pioneers. She was invited by Amazon to the India launch of the Kindle.</span>
